SIMPLE: cantoned
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cantoned
<hw>Can"toned</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Having a charge in each of the four corners; --
said of a cross on a shield, and also of the shield itself.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>Having the angles marked by, or
decorated with, projecting moldings or small columns; <as>as, a
<ex>cantoned</ex> pier or pilaster</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Canton flannel</ent>⟦br⟧
